cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is about dense captioning, which is a computer vision task that involves understanding images with dense language descriptions. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model pipeline based on joint inference and context fusion, which involves natural language processing techniques, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates variations in architecture and achieves state-of-the-art accuracy, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes a new model architecture to address the challenges of dense captioning, which involves recognizing visual concepts, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves experiments with visual data, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
